The paper discusses challenges in teaching logic and formal methods to Computer Science and IT students, which is a topic that falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The course is also aimed at engineering students, which could potentially fall under the category of Engineering and Control Systems (cs.ED). The paper also discusses the goal of engaging students and making the subject less boring, which could fall under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents examples of exercises and evaluates the course, which could fall under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL).
